The source code for Cozie is open source and [freely available on Github](https://github.com/cozie-app/cozie-apple).


You need to have an Apple computer running iOS and [XCode](https://developer.apple.com/xcode/) to modify and compile the Cozie source code.

# Setup Cozie in Xcode and run it in a Simulator
1. Download the Cozie source code from [Github](https://github.com/cozie-app/cozie-apple).
2. Install CocoaPods
3. Open the project file with XCode
4. Create an iPhone simulator device
5. Create an Apple Watch simulator device
6. Compile Cozie for the Apple Watch simulator and run it
7. Compile Cozie for the iPhone simulator and run it

# Create your own Cozie version
1. Create new identifiers
2. Create a new app
3. Create a OneSignal account
4. Create a OneSignal app
5. Connect your Cozie version with your OneSignal app
6. Compile your Cozie version for TestFlight
7. Publish you Cozie version on the AppStore
